A 58-year-old man was stabbed to death at his farm in Atlantis, police said. CAPE TOWN - Police say arrests have yet to be made after a 58-year-old man was stabbed to death at his farm in Atlantis. The victim's wife and another man were also injured in the attack on Thursday evening. Four armed men are believed to have attacked the family after gaining access to their property. The police's Andre Traut says: "The suspect left with household items and arrests are yet to be made. Any person with information is kindly requested to contact Crime Stop at 08600 10111."